{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 14:08:15.106562", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and Objective\n- Assess end-to-end health of the enterprise OSPF network and application reachability for DNS and HTTP services.\n- Detect anomalies, localize faulty devices, and identify likely root cause(s).\n\nSummary of Network Health\n- Routing/OSPF: Healthy. End-to-end ICMP reachability across user subnets (10.<core>.<dist>.0/24) and the server farm (10.200.0.0/24) is consistently successful with 0% loss and low RTTs. Examples:\n  - Hosts to servers: host_1_1_1_1 -> 10.200.0.2/.3/.6/.7 all reachable (0% loss, ~3–7 ms).\n  - Cross-host connectivity: host_1_1_1_1 <-> host_2_1_1_1 OK.\n  - Server-to-host and server-to-server pings OK.\n- DHCP: Both hosts obtained dynamic addresses and default gateways (10.1.1.10 via 10.1.1.1, 10.2.1.10 via 10.2.1.1), indicating relay and server are working.\n- DNS: Name resolution from hosts works for local zone:\n  - getent on host_1_1_1_1 resolves: web0.local -> 10.200.0.3, web3.local -> 10.200.0.6, web99.local -> 10.200.0.7.\n\nHTTP/Application Reachability Findings\n- Load balancer (web99.local at 10.200.0.7): Healthy.\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> http://web99.local succeeds repeatedly; TTFB ~0.21–0.27 s; total ~1.0–1.07 s.\n- Web servers web1.local and web2.local: Healthy.\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> http://web1.local and http://web2.local succeed; total ~1.1–1.7 s.\n- Web server web3.local: Healthy.\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> http://web3.local succeeds; total ~1.02–1.35 s.\n- Web server web0.local (10.200.0.3): Abnormal—HTTP service non-responsive.\n  - Timeouts from multiple independent sources:\n    - host_1_1_1_1 -> http://web0.local and http://10.200.0.3 both time out (>10 s).\n    - host_2_1_1_1 -> http://web0.local timeouts.\n    - dns_server and load_balancer -> http://10.200.0.3 timeouts.\n  - ICMP to 10.200.0.3 succeeds, indicating IP connectivity and routing are fine; failure is specific to TCP/HTTP application response.\n\nHost/Server Local Checks and Evidence\n- web_server_0 (10.200.0.3):\n  - Port 80 is listening: ss/netstat shows 0.0.0.0:80 LISTEN by python3 (PID 44).\n  - Apache service: inactive (dead). iptables policy: ACCEPT (no DROP rules observed).\n  - Local loopback HTTP also fails: curl to http://127.0.0.1/ on web_server_0 times out (>10 s).\n  - These point to an application-level failure (listener present but not processing connections) rather than network or firewall issues.\n- web_server_1 and web_server_2:\n  - Apache reported inactive (dead), yet external HTTP requests succeed. This suggests an alternate HTTP service is running (not validated further), and there is no user-visible issue for these nodes.\n- Backend server accessibility:\n  - Attempt to reach “backend_web_0” returns “Destination Net Unreachable” via gateway. Given the design states backend web servers should not be directly accessible from hosts, this behavior is expected.\n\nAnomalies Detected\n- Complete HTTP application failure on web_server_0 (10.200.0.3):\n  - Symptom: TCP/HTTP connections hang and time out from multiple vantage points (hosts, DNS server, load balancer), while ICMP is OK.\n  - Localization: web_server_0 itself (issue reproduces locally on 127.0.0.1).\n  - Network layers (L2/L3), OSPF routing, DNS, and firewalls show no faults related to this issue.\n- Minor observation: apache2 on several web servers shows inactive; however, only web_server_0 exhibits an actual service outage. Others serve HTTP successfully (likely via a different process).\n\nImpact Assessment\n- Direct access to web0.local (10.200.0.3) is unavailable due to HTTP timeouts.\n- Load-balanced service (web99.local) remains healthy, so user access via the load balancer is unaffected.\n- Other individual web servers (web1.local, web2.local, web3.local) are reachable and responsive.\n\nRoot Cause Assessment\n- Root cause is localized to the HTTP application on web_server_0.\n  - Evidence: Port 80 listening by python3 but no response to local or remote HTTP requests; apache2 inactive; no firewall blocks; ICMP OK.\n  - Most likely an application hang/unresponsive process on web_server_0.\n\nNo Remediation Provided (per instructions)\n- This report focuses on detection, localization, and root cause identification without proposing mitigation steps.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9746, "output_tokens": 3534, "total_tokens": 13280, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9216}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2368}}}
